@startuml
title Observer Pattern - Before

class FlightOrder {
    - flights: List<ScheduledFlight>
    - {static} noFlyList: List<String>
    + FlightOrder(flights: List<ScheduledFlight>)
    + getScheduledFlights(): List<ScheduledFlight>
    + processOrder(paymentStrategy: PaymentStrategy): boolean
}

class Order {
    - id: UUID
    - price: double
    - isClosed: boolean
    - customer: Customer
    - passengers: List<Passenger>
    + getPrice(): double
    + isClosed(): boolean
    + setClosed()
}

note right of FlightOrder
  processOrder() pays and closes the order.
  No notification mechanism exists.
  Any post-payment concerns (confirmation,
  capacity alerts, audit logs, loyalty points)
  would have to be added directly inside
  processOrder() — coupling FlightOrder
  to every downstream concern.
  Each new notification type requires
  modifying FlightOrder.
end note

FlightOrder --|> Order

@enduml
